Title: 1977 MG - MGB MK IV Roadster
Description: Come on now, you know you want one! A fully restored MGB MK IV Roadster that is. And that's exactly what your looking at here. Enter this premium example of one of Britain's most iconic sport cars. Manufactured by the British Motor Corporation from 1962 through 1980 the MGB was to become one of a family of MG's biggest sellers, with over a half a million examples being sold throughout the series. Light, agile and super fun to drive are just some of the hallmarks of this little beauty. In this cars case there is little left of the patina that is usually associated with cars of this era as it has been fully refurbished from top to bottom and front to rear. Just about everything has been lovingly replaced with new old stock components and where original parts could not be found, the substitution of some very high quality aftermarket parts have been used. New wiring harness, updated cooling system, complete with new radiator, hoses, thermostat, water pump as well as the stock pulley driven cooling and a supplemental electric cooling fan system to boot. Look closely at the pictures and you will see the results of countless hours of work and dollars invested in the restoration of the car. The car runs, drives and handles better than new. Come on down to Raphael Luxury Motor Cars and take a trip in this "way back time machine" and experience for yourself a little slice of motoring history "British" style! Call 360-373-6758 for more information on this sweet little roadster. And, like we always say, "Don't Dream It, Drive It" and "We'll See You When You Get Here".

Title: 1996 Jeep XJ Cherokee Sport
Description: For sale is a bone stock 1996 Jeep Cherokee Sport This is a 4.0L XJ @ ~206k miles with an automatic AW4 transmission, Dana 30/35 and an NP242. It's in pretty good condition with some cosmetic dents to the body, some missing parts and cracks in the interior/dash- but otherwise in pretty great shape and has no rust. Has been used as both a daily driver and a 4x4(works) weekend adventure-mobile since I've gotten it and has never let me down from the coast all the way to snoqualmie pass. As far as I can tell the heat and A/C work but the fans don't blow very hard. I have replaced the oil filter adapter seal, motor mounts, transmission mount, rear diff has been refilled and sealed. I have done regular oil changes and changed the transmission fluid a few months ago. Door brackets/pins and liftgate support struts have also been replaced, and I installed a Pioneer usb/cd receiver. It has virtually brand new Goodyear Wrangler 225r75 tires on it (purchased ~4k miles ago - not pictured).Here is the build sheet directly from Jeep: https://www.jeep.com/webselfservice/BuildSheetServlet?vin=1J4FJ68S1TL310056Cons: When replacing the motor mounts, I discovered that a bolt that mounts the bracket to the passenger side engine engine is shorn off into the block - so it is held on by two out of three bolts(I replaced with grade 8). I have not had any issues with this setup, but it is something you should be aware of. Also, I believe either the RMS or Valve Cover Gasket is leaking ever so slightly, which is pretty typical for 4.0L Jeeps. I haven't had to top off oil in between changes so I think this is a *very* slow leak.Bike racks/dogs are not included.Asking $3000 cash. I'm not in any sort of hurry to sell this, but am willing to entertain offers. I will consider trades for high-end steel bicycles, CF road bikes, vintage synthesizers, or acoustic guitars. Clean title is in hand. E-mail if interested.

Title: 1996 Toyota 4Runner SR5
Description: 262k miles, Runs and drives, needs brake rotors and pads, belt squeaks. 2wd, not 4x4, (like you'd find one less than 2k)I bought this from someone who let it sit for a year because they couldn't get it running.  I got it a new battery and changed out most of the vacuum hoses, now it starts any time you turn the key.  It idles at the proper rpms at idle and under load.  It shifts at the correct times while driving and has no problems going into reverse.  I have been told the overdrive does not work.I don't know the last time the timing belt/water pump was changed, but it's a 4Runner for under 2k that runs and drives, not a brand new car!Needs some body work, and a good cleaning of the inside.

Title: 1985 Subaru Brat
Description: 1985 Subaru BRAT GLClean and clear title in my nameRuns and drives greatOdometer is not accurate, the dash and cluster are from another car. True mileage unknown.I love this Brat and have had a lot of fun with it, but it is time to pass it on for someone else to enjoy. I've done a lot of work over the past couple years, so mechanically it is really solid! It could use some cosmetic attention, but I just don't have the time to do it. The black stuff you see in the door jambs and under the hood is Ziebart rust protection done when the car was new. This would be a perfect Brat for somebody with the time to finish the bodywork. As it sits, it's a cool survivor with some great mods and rare parts that gets tons of smiles and waves every time I drive it!New parts, upgrades, and good Brat stuff!-Resealed stock EA81 with SPFI fuel injection swap.-Brand new aftermarket header and catalytic converter, 2005 WRX muffler-New starter-New electric fuel pump, new fuel filter-5-speed dual range swap, new clutch and resurfaced flywheel, I used all the stock interior trim and 4wd lever-New waterpump, new radiator-Resealed and rebuilt oil pump-New front CV axles-New front ball joints-New brakes front and rear, new master cylinder-Rear disc brake swap from turbo Subaru RX-14" Peugeot steel wheels-New (slightly oversized) General Altimax Arctic studless snow tires-One extra 14" Peugeot wheel and extra spares of the special Pug lugnuts-Set of 4 Peugeot wheel center caps (Rare!)-Many extra SPFI spare parts, basically enough to do another whole swap. ECU, distributor, two throttle bodies, extra harness, sensors, etc.-All bed chrome intact and in good condition!-Have good condition seats and seat frame for the bed, previous owner removed them-Working factory AM/FM stereo-GemTop canopy-Aftermarket trailer hitch with 2" ball-Spare set of 13" black steel Subaru wheels with decent but old tiresSome bad things:-Some rust at the front of the rockers needs to be repaired, a little in the bed, but overall it's pretty solid for a Brat. Previous owner coated some of the surface rust in the bed with some sort of epoxy.-Steering wheel vibration at highway speed that I haven't been able to solve. Might be the new front CV axles, or some bushings or something like that. I have a set of front axle stubs to convert to RWD to troubleshoot this problem.-Driver's seat needs recovered-Two rock chips with cracks in the corners of the windshield, not in the way while driving

Title: 2005 Buick LeSabre
Description: Up for sale is a 2005 Buick Le Sabre Custom. Car has 131,xxx miles, It's a very reliable car. I've never had any issues with it. I've owned it since the vehicle had around 60,000 miles on, I used it as my daily driver until about 8/2015. I have driven it every other week to keep it running and in good shape. It has a new battery from 2017, the tires have less than 10,000 miles on them, purchased tires 4/2015 from Costco. The outside of the car does have a few dents/scratches here and there, nothing to really diminish the beauty of it. As for the interior it's in fairly good shape. There is 1 small burn hole in between the driver and passenger seat and the back seat has some spots on it as well from when my son was a baby. The steering wheel has faded a bit as well from use. Otherwise it looks great, doesn't smell or have any odors. Recently had oil change and a tie rod replaced, only needs an alignment. I plan on getting that done soon, unless it sells first.Sound package Addition/Upgrade if you're interested: I have a new upgraded double din Radio with all needed adapters to attach to steering wheel controls, etc.. Title: 98 Tahoe LT
Description: 5.7 ltr V8 Vortec. 4x4. Clean title. Brand new plugs and egr valve. Fantastic engine but rough idle. Fuel gauge not working properly so possible fuel pump issue is cause of rough idle. Inside driver interior handle not working and left passenger door doesnt open. Shakey steering wheel. New rotors and rims may do the trick. Tires in good condition. Solid and strong transmission.  Only used Chevron fuel with Techron and oil changes at 1500 mile intervals.  All lights inside and out work. There are no leaks whatsoever.  Been very dependable until rough idle started just a week ago. Hard to part with this vehicle. Great  sentimental value. I've driven this for 8 years and never once had an issue. Until a week ago with the rough idle and shakey steering wheel. I know there is much more this Tahoe has got in it to offer. Maybe think about it before just parting it out. Just needs a couple things fixed. This Tahoe will need to be towed until the fuel gage and pump are fixed. $30 part. I have given an honest accurate account. Make offer. Thanks for reading.

Title: 2002 BMW X5 4.4i Sport Silver w/Black Leather Clean Title
Description: For sale is my Silver 2002 BMW X5 4.4i (V8) E53 with Sport Package (5-Speed Automatic Transmission with Sport and Manual mode).  The car is currently not fully operational: transmission is throwing error/code (see details below): it goes into "Trans Failsafe" mode which is 5th gear, so technically will drive under its own power once it gets going, but not recommended for long distance: I recommend towing it away. Sports Package (difference to regular/base 4.4i) is: 19" Wheels specific to Sport Package V8 X5s, Sport Seats with Thicker Side Bolsters and Adjustable Thigh Support w/3-Setting Memory, 3-Spoke Sport Steering Wheel (with Audio and Phone controls), Stiffer/lower suspension with rear air suspension tuned for sportier ride and handling). Other desirable options are: * Class 3 (2") Trailer Hitch Receiver:  Towing capacity of this X5 is rated at 6,000 lbs with trailer brakes. * BMW Navigation System with 6-CD Changer in trunk * HomeLink (programmable home & garage door opener)* Myrtle Wood Trim / HID Xenon Headlights  VIN: 5UXFB33512LH35408 2002 BMW X5 4.4i Sport Engine: 4.4L V8 32-Valve 290 horsepower @5400rpm / 324 lb-ft torque @3600rpm Exterior Color: Silver [Good Condition 7/10] Interior Color: Black Leather [Excellent Condition 9/10] Title: Clean Washington State title in my name.  This is my personal car and a private sale.  Free of liens.  Title in hand ready for immediate transfer.Accidents:  None.  Verified with VIN History check and general condition of the car History:  Originally a California car, and then lived in Washington state the remainder of its life.  So NO RUST. Mileage:  133,440 miles [accurate as read from ECU/instrument cluster via scanner software (even though you cannot see from gauge cluster): I have printout as proof.]Pros:* Sport Package, Clean exterior and interior, Towing Package, Accident-Free, Clean Title * Relatively new tires (Nitto Motivo performance all-season tires), plenty of life left* Relatively new brake rotors/pads* Recent ignition coil replacement with Bavarian Autosport units (all 8) & engine tune-up* Entire cooling system (weak point in these cars due to all the plastic components) has been replaced: new water pump, belts, tensioners, radiator, coolant hoses/pipes* All electrical functions work: door remote, windows, lights, locks, sunroof, rain-sensing wipers, rear suspension air bags, etc. * Car starts up without drama every time  * I am the 3rd ownerCons: * Transmission has an issue, but I don't know exactly what.  When I read the codes in INPA, it states that slippage is detected: input and output speeds different.     The previous owner, who daily drove it for 8+ years, had the transmission rebuilt and said that after a few months, it started to slip and it would throw the "Trans Failsafe" error which locks the transmission into 5th gear (making it hard to get going from a standstill or uphill, but once you get going, the car will drive).     The car will slip from 1st gear, and when it senses the slip, it will go into limp mode.  Reverse gear is totally fine, no slippage and drives normal.  It's the forward gears.     I bought the car in this condition from the car's 2nd owner (who had it for almost 10 years), thinking it would be an easy fix (I experienced the same symptoms on my other X5, and it was the ABS Module that needed to be rebuilt).  I suspected the valve body, as is common in this ZF 5HP24 transmission, so recently (May 2018) I dropped the transmission oil pan, cleaned it up (no metal shavings on the magnets), replaced the filter, o-ring, and gasket, and flushed and refilled the transmission fluid a total of 4 times with Pentosin ATF1 fluid (recommended fluid per ZF and BMW).  I removed the valve body and replaced with a brand new unit from RevMax Converters in North Carolina (they specialize in performance automatic transmissions:  https://revmaxconverters.com/ ).  All-in-all cost for this was over $1000.  But unfortunately, the symptoms are still there.  I don't know what else might be the issue and now I don't have much time and losing the space to store the car, so looking to sell.Other than that, no huge issues: just some minor things:* Front passenger door handle carrier is broken (replacement is ~$20 each and not terribly hard to do): so must be opened from the inside (or lower down windows using key remote fob and pull handle from inside).* Left driver's side mirror is cracked and the heated mirror's oil spilled out* Fuel gauge doesn't register, shows empty even after I put in 6 gallons of fuel.  Computer scanning software shows that fuel level sensor is faulty, so change that out.* Fog light warning: front left bulb out (H3 Bulb ~$8)* Pixels missing in gauge cluster (super common issue), so cannot make out exact mileage [can read via scanner, though]* Pixels missing in navigation screen* Hazy headlights: could use a polish* Normal wear and tear for a 16-year old used car.  2 cuts in the rear bumper and scratch (from being keyed?) on the left rear quarter panel is the worst of it.Car is worth more in parts, but I don't have the space or time to part it out.  You can buy and part it yourself and recoup your purchase, or if you are handy and know these cars, you can attempt to fix the transmission and have a nice X5.Pre-Purchase Inspection (PPI) will be on your dime, but I will help out as best as I can (keep in mind I can't drive it to the station, so you'll have to pay to have it towed there and back).  Test drive / in-person inspection for serious buyers are OK.  Recent (6/2018) VIN History Report and AutoCheck VIN Report available upon request.Currently located in Issaquah, WA.  Looking to sell for cash only.In your email, please say what city you are located (this is to filter out spam and generic emails such as "Is the car still available?" or "Will you sell for $X?" which I will not answer).  *** If the ad is up, it is still available.  I will take it down as soon as I have cash in hand and therefore the buyer has the title.  *** Thank you for reading.Edit: The car does not have the running boards as shown in the photos as I swapped them out with my other X5.  I have uploaded a few photos of it in its current condition without them.

Title: Panoz Esperante Roadster
Description: Up for sale is my 2002 Panoz Esperante roadster.If you are not familiar with these, they are a low-volume, hand-built car by race car fabricators Panoz in Georgia.  They start with the mechanicals from a Mustang Cobra SVT, which include a hand-built 4.6 liter 32-valve overhead cam aluminum V8 with a 5-speed manual T45 transmission, connected to the Cobra IRS rear suspension with limited slip differential.  The engine is 320 HP, making for spirited performance.The body and frame are fabricated of aluminum and carbon fiber.  The interior has leather power seats, A/C, cruise, power windows, power mirrors, traction control, power top, and a nice stereo. So it is like an exotic car in appearance, performance and construction (same market as Porsche, Ferrari, Lamborghini, Lotus), but it can be repaired and maintained with parts available from Ford and local parts suppliers.  Panoz also sells parts for the car.The car is in excellent condition, both mechanically and cosmetically.  It has about 75,000 miles (less than 5,000 per year).  The original owner had the car in Utah until about 2015, with the CarFAX showing regular servicing.  The front fascia was recently repainted to eliminate paint chips that have occurred through the years, it has a new battery, and the rear shock absorbers were recently rebuilt and recalibrated for better performance.  It includes the factory tool kit and owners manual.NADA shows these with an average retail value of $56,000.  As a low volume, high performance car, they should appreciate through the years, making for a sound investment.  I believe that the total production run was about 235 cars.The car can be viewed at my home between Marysville and Arlington.  Test drives for serious buyers on dry days only please.

Title: USDM 1996 Toyota Supra MK4 V160 Single Turbo Tuned *Clean Title*
Description: I've lowered the price for the time being because I found the GT3 I want to buy. Price is 100% firm.Posting a feeler ad to see if I get any interest on my MK4 Supra. It's my pride and joy. I've been building this car from when I was 16 until now. It started off as a N/A. Not accepting any trades at this time and no I don't need any help or assistance selling this car.I've had this car for the most part of my older life. I can honestly say, I've done almost everything I'll list to this car with the exception of the new clutch, flywheel, transmission, driveshaft, and rear differential which was replaced at Intec Racing in Kent, WA. I've driven it maybe 200 miles since.I'll keep it as simple as possible, if you're truly interested contact me for more details.- Clean Title- 1996 - Toyota Supra - Originally a N/A. But I've literally swapped everything you can put on a turbo car on this one and more!- JDM 2JZGTE with around 84k now by my calculations. I still warm her up once in a while and drive her around when I'm in town. - V160 and entire drivetrain have less than 200 miles on them since I installed it.- T-61 SPBudget Turbo Kit;Tuned very conservatively on 16psi. Makes just under 500RWHP and that's more than enough for me.- Wahlbro 255 Fuel Pump - 550CC Injectors, if you want to make more power just upgrade injectors and retune. - FMIC with all piping and BOV flange welded in.- Exhaust is custom made and fitted with 2 catalytic converters so it actually passed Smog in California even with the Single Turbo kit.- Apexi Intake - Turbo Heat Wrap- HKS SS BOV- MAP ECU standalone - Samco Hoses- Megan Radiator - Megan Upgraded Thermostat- Greddy Strut Tower- Greddy Turbo Timer- Recaro Confetti Seats. (I also have a pair of Recaro Pole Positions as well that can be negotiated into the deal for an additional amount.)- Tein Suspension- 19" Gramlight 57s Pros with Titanium Lip. Staggered. New Rear Tires (I've never seen another supra, let alone any other car with these wheels.)- Rotora BBK all around, front and rear.- OEM 98+ Taillights- Boost and Oil Pressure/Temp Gauge- OEM UKDM Glass headlights, stupid rare and expensive if you can find them. Prevents all the haze and any issues you'll ever have in the future with headlights.- The entire interior is brand new. I have all the old plastic interior pieces so you can see what I've bought. There is literally over 8-9k worth of interior pieces I've bought brand new from Toyota. Some are still in the bags unopened. I'm meticulous and I would prefer it to be perfect. Still needs the rear trunk pieces installed. The paint is Aspen White. It was out of commission for over a year and over 100 man hours of labor getting this car to look as nice as she does. No corners were cut. The paint is virtually flawless.- Stillen side skirts and front bumper- Personal Detchable Steering Wheel- APR CF Mirrors (Not Installed.)- Pioneer Bluetooth audio/aux/iPod enabled indash.-  New Toyota Floor Mats- Oil always changed with Motul every 5,000 miles.- VIS Carbon Fiber HoodThere is a ton of stuff I am forgetting to list. Just know I've had this car for nearly 15 years, it's moved with me to California and back to Washington and even for a 5 year period, had exchanged owners to one of my friends in LA who put no more than 500 miles on it in 5 years!39,500 and you get everything else extra for it. I have about 8-9k worth of parts most still in the bag brand new from Toyota. Recaro Pole Positions can be bought for an additional 2,000.

Title: K2500 suburban 4x4
Description: This is a strong, heavy duty truck.  The exterior is excellent, other than the paint fading on the hood.  Interior is great, but needs some little things like a heater control knob and little things like that.  The driver seat is a bit messed up, one of the bracket bolts that holds the front left corner down is broken and the front of the headliner sags a little bit.  Engine runs and it drives, but is losing coolant somewhere, it's not in the oil though.  It could definitely use a tune up.  I don't have the time or money to put into it, with a little TLC it will be a fantastic rig.

Title: 2001 Toyota Corolla
Description: 2001 Toyota Corolla with 245,000 miles. Great little hooptie for commuting or first time driver.  This is an 18 year old car so no she's not the prettiest and yes there are some minor mechanical issues. It burns oil, I check it every two weeks and get it maitananced reqularly. I was hit while parked in a parking lot so there is a nice ding on the rear side.  Tabs are due this month and there is a crack in the windshield. Again, 18 year old car for under $1000. Looking for a good home for this awesome little Car.Thank you,Jason

I'm extremely anal with my work everything is first class. The body is low mileage very straight no rust. Title: 1985 Nissan 720 ST King Cab (Permanent Oregon Registration!)
Description: This is an extremely well maintained Nissan ST with everything in perfect working order. I bought it last year from the second owner of 23 years. He took amazing care of this truck. Unfortunately I have to sell for financial reasons but hope it goes to another enthusiast. Good tread on the tires, locking canapy topper painted to match white paint job. Has new Pioneer CD player stereo with USB and aux input. Runs like a dream. Has factory pop up sunroof which is removable, factory power windows, factory clock and tachometer. A really well designed truck with lots of cool options but no AC. Has mechanical carburator from an 84 720 which works way better than the early fuel injection system it came with and is larger and more effective than a Webber setup. Comes with a few extra parts the previous owner gave me like an extra glass for the sunroof. Has jump seats in back area too. Interior is in great shape, no issues. 140k miles. Registered in Oregon with yellow period plates that come with the truck. Never needs to be paid for every year like a normal registration as it is a Special Interest tag as a classic vehicle. 5 Speed manual transmission, 2.4 liter NapZ in line 4 cylinder. Come check it out, you won't be disappointed! ThanksScott

Title: 1990 Toyota 4Runner LOW MILES
Description: Selling this 1990 Toyota 4Runner. I love these cars and always wanted one. I bought this about a week ago. It runs, drives and stops. It needs some work so I thought I'd take a stab at fixing it. But I give up because I'm not that mechanically inclined I guess. I'll list the goods and bads. Good:Body is actually in pretty good shapeInterior is in good shapeTires have good tread leftPower rear window works normally Brand new oil and filterBrand new front wipersBrand new rear shocksBrand new transmission fluidBrand new transmission filter AND all 3 shifter solenoid'sBrand new air filterAll the seats are in good shape. No rips or tears. Registration tabs are current. Bad:-Needs power steering hose or pump. Leaking from somewhere. -Leaks oil-Transmission shifts in and out of gear and flashes a code for shifter solenoid number three. I've already replaced it so I don't know what's wrong. Maybe a loose connection? I don't have the time or money to invest into this. But for the price, you have a great start so a great ride. Very low mileage for the age.Will probably need to be towed although I just drove it home from Bothel without a tow. Come get it today! Thanks. Dean

The headlights lenses and busted but lights still work and the transfer case has a little play in it so there is a clunk when shifting sometimes ( typical on these vehicles) I have new valve cover gaskets to be put on. Leaks a little oil from there but nothing major at all. I drive this car every single day it's great and reliable just needs a little love call or text flexible on the price

Description: Hello, I am selling this car that I bought just 2 months ago. I'm a foreigner who had some holiday here, but I need to leave soon, so I'm selling it. DEQ just done, and a car inspection too.The previous owner told me everything works well, but not really.-There is a leak somewhere. I don't know what it is. After driving a while, it can smell like burned oil. But I didn't have any problem.-Car mechanic said that one front lower suspension ball joint should be changed in the future.-Odometer doesn't work, except those last days, it started to run again, but randomly (from previous owner, who had the car for 1 year, the odometer stopped to work 6 months ago. So have to add around 5000 miles from previous owner, and no more than 4 thousands from me. Cheap to fix)-(Previous owner) Small dent in driver rear quarter panel from a low impact collision in parking lot, superficial damage.-Rear right door don't open from inside. Back door don't lock with the keyless entry, have to do it manually (previous owner)-All leather in correct condition4 wheel drive V-6 w/Automatic transmissionA/C6-disc CD playerDual power seatsŒæNewer batteryNew tires-Extra set of tires included. Gets around 20-25mpg-Plate is from Washington state.-Tags are expired-Title from Oregon. I still don't have it in hands, cause I was traveling. DMV told me they can send it to the new owner address, so no problem.I m selling it 1300. I think it is fair for someone who has some times to fix the problems.Feel free to contact meThanks

1977 Jeep J20 4WD Flatbed
Description: Located West of the Hood Canal Bridge. Location is on the map.Runs and drives! Hard to start after sitting for a while, but when driven regularly he's a CHAMP!  Needs a new tranny, leaks fluid (we just top it off now and then). Also could use a new battery, but starts without a jump if driven again within a day or two. The odometer says 92,594 but it has probably rolled over.Has custom wood racks for the sides and back of the bed.I think it's a V8 but I'm not sure.Tires are in awesome shape.Windshield has a crack.Clean title in hand.I'm not a mechanic and I haven't done any work on him since I got him 3 years back. Besides being hard to start and needing a tranny fluid top-off, he's been great. Has hauled huge heaping loads of hay without an issue, and crawled through my pasture and over creeks several times without a hitch.Hands-down the coolest truck I've ever owned, but I don't drive him often enough and he hates sitting. Needs to be spruced up and driven all the time!Oh, the exterior pictures were taken the day I got him. He's back to being a little mossy! Interior and tire pictures are brand new.

Title: 1997 honda civic 1450 obo
Description: Our Green Bastard is ready for a new home. We purchased this magnificent unicorn from my wonderful neighbours to begin rally crossing. It twas their sons car through out his fine addolesencent years of high school and a bit further. Then he purchased a new vehicle and then it was left to wither, sad, vacant, with glorious cultures of new forms of un-discovered life forms colmbinating together in a wonderful brew of discarded Wendy's frosty cups combined with left over cigarette butts. Out of the catacombs of the rear lounge we mined out a few nuggets of a substance (I was educated later) to be called "Hash." Further more empty premium lager cans of Rainer Beer co. In stock piles would have procured enough funds in our sister state oregon to indeed not only purchase but repair the vehicle to safe WaDOT standards.My beautiful, although stubborn wife agreed to purchase this car so our two beautiful faces could begin rally crossing! Super fun I know right! OMG it is!We.....I.... repaired the car to optimum standards for "stock class" everything is stock, minus the muffler.The newTiming belt and water pumpBatteryRadiatorBrakes, front and rearEvery motor mountValve coverSpark plugsClutch slave cylinderSnow tires all around even full size spare and snow tireAnd not to go un noticed the beautiful picasso green deck paint and whiskey influenced paint job. The badIm a mechanic and have not found anything worth deeming this vehicle unworthy. Other than an airbag light whitch... who crashes in a rally anyways come on folks. Annnnd the trunk always says its open. I can repair with a simple jumper wire if you prefer.Anything that wiggled before does not now and is solid, we own a shop in bellevue and i even alligned the car after every race (3 in total) to make sure nothing was hurt.Our last race the original exhaust manifold gave way but i have a brand spankning new one provided on a slow boat enroute from china. Will be installed at no expense to you if you purchase before the aforementioned "boat," arrives. We have replaced the green bastard with an AWD rally car for more smiles per gallon. But its time for our hondr to goThis honda runs great! If you would like to test drive this powerhouse of a tuna can Feel free to contact me via txt with any questions, or ridicule who cares!Everything is for sale just make a decent offer.

Title: 2004 Subaru Forester XS w recent head gasket replacement
Description: Traveling soon so must sell my car. It's been a trooper and I have used it as a work vehicle so the inside is not immaculate by any means but it's clean and priced to sell. Runs and drives great. 157k miles, head gasket was replaced at 135k with ignition coil and plugs.Issues:Brake pads squeal on occasion. The les schwab dudes said they're fine just noisy.Struts will probably need to be replaced at some point. When driving over potholes you can hear them working. Check engine light code P0457 is on. I just put a new gas cap on so I'll update if it turns off with that. Doesn't seem like a big issue to fix and it runs fine. I just don't have the time to deal with it. Come check it out, feel free to get at me with questions. I will absolutely need it gone by the end of July. It could use some love but the engine is strong and ready to go for a long time. Custom roof rack optional ;)
